`` To Change node version of a project we have some commands. ``

1. Install NVM it will take control of the present Node 

Link to download NVM
https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows/releases

2. Download:
nvm-setup.exe (latest release)

3. Open PowerShell and run:
nvm version
Step 1: Install Node 16 (Keep Node 24!)
nvm install 16

Step 2: Switch to Node 16 (Safe Switch)
nvm use 16

Step 3: Now verify:

node -v
npm -v

Step 4: Reinstall dependencies for THIS project only

Go to your project folder:

cd E:\00-frontend-starting-setup ( Replace with real directory )

Step 5: Clean old install (required):

rmdir /s /q node_modules
del package-lock.json

Step 6: Install again:

npm install

Step 7: Start the project
npm start


Switching Back to Node 24 Anytime

For another project:

nvm use 24
node -v
